# SHARED by BOTH Vercel projects — the repo-root .vercelignore is read by the
# web project (Root Directory apps/web) AND the Python worker (Root Directory .).
# Only list files that NEITHER project needs.
#
# Purpose: hide the uv/pyproject project files so the worker's Python build falls
# back to the slim root requirements.txt instead of installing the full ~654 MB
# project from uv.lock (over Vercel's 500 MB limit). Neither the Next.js web app
# nor the worker needs these at build time.
#
# DO NOT add source directories here (e.g. apps/web, apps/local) — they get
# stripped from EVERY project, which empties the web app's build and 404s it.
# The worker's own function bundle is trimmed separately via excludeFiles in
# vercel.json.
uv.lock
pyproject.toml
